{
  "question_id": "82b8990a-c4ef-4d52-81a1-ebc097dfc7ae",
  "short_text": "Butterfly - 2",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print a **Butterfly** of `2 * N` rows using stars (`*`).\r\n\r\n```\r\n*                 * \r\n* *             * * \r\n* * *         * * * \r\n* * * *     * * * * \r\n* * * * * * * * * * \r\n* * * * * * * * * * \r\n* * * *     * * * * \r\n* * *         * * * \r\n* *             * * \r\n*                 * \r\n```\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nThere is a space after every star (`*`).\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Input\r\n\r\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Output\r\n\r\nThe output should be `2 * N` rows containing stars (`*`) as a **Butterfly** shown in the sample output.\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Explanation\r\n\r\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 5`, \r\n\r\n- Print the stars (`*`) on **10** (`2 * 5`) rows as shown in the given image.\r\n\r\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-butterfly-2.png' widthPercent='80'/>\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\nIn the given image,\r\n\r\n- The Empty box indicates two spaces (\"&nbsp;&nbsp;\").\r\n- The Star in the box indicates the star and a space (\"* \").\r\n\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\nThe output should be,\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n*                 * \r\n* *             * * \r\n* * *         * * * \r\n* * * *     * * * * \r\n* * * * * * * * * * \r\n* * * * * * * * * * \r\n* * * *     * * * * \r\n* * *         * * * \r\n* *             * * \r\n*                 * \r\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "800134ce-7aa9-4f72-b38a-79e249c7499c",
      "code_content": "n = int(input())\n\nfor i in range(1, n + 1):\n    stars = \"* \" * i\n    middle_spaces = \"  \" * (2 * (n - i))\n    print(stars + middle_spaces + stars)\n\nfor i in range(n):\n    stars = \"* \" * (n - i)\n    middle_spaces = \"  \" * (2 * i)\n    print(stars + middle_spaces + stars)\n",
